# Implementation Report: Vercel Web Analytics Integration

## Summary
Successfully integrated Vercel Web Analytics into the BAS Vue.js application following the official Vercel documentation guidelines.

## Changes Made

### 1. Installed Dependencies
- Added `@vercel/analytics` package to project dependencies
- Updated `package.json` and `package-lock.json` with the new package

### 2. Integrated Analytics Component
**File Modified:** `src/App.vue`
- Imported the `Analytics` component from `@vercel/analytics/vue`
- Added the `<Analytics />` component to the main app template
- Placed it at the top of the app div, before router-view and ToastContainer components

This implementation follows the Vue.js framework instructions from the Vercel Web Analytics guide, which states:
> "The `Analytics` component is a wrapper around the tracking script, offering more seamless integration with Vue."
> "Route support is automatically enabled if you're using `vue-router`."

Since this project uses `vue-router`, route tracking will be automatic.

### 3. Fixed Pre-existing Build Error
**File Modified:** `src/components/common/Navbar.vue`
- Removed duplicate `</style>` closing tag (line 337)
- This was a pre-existing syntax error preventing the build from completing

