### Expected Behavior
Once deployed to Vercel:
- Analytics tracking will automatically start recording page views
- Route changes will be tracked automatically due to vue-router integration
- Fetch/XHR requests to `/_vercel/insights/view` will be visible in browser Network tab
- Data will be available in the Vercel Dashboard under the Analytics tab

## Implementation Details

The integration follows the Vue.js-specific instructions from Vercel's official guide:
```vue
import { Analytics } from '@vercel/analytics/vue';
<Analytics />
```

The component is placed at the root level of the application to ensure it's initialized early and can track all route changes throughout the app lifecycle.

## Next Steps for Deployment

To complete the setup:
1. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel Dashboard (Project → Analytics → Enable)
2. Deploy the application to Vercel using `vercel deploy` or via Git integration
3. Verify analytics are working by checking for `/_vercel/insights/view` requests
4. View data in the Vercel Dashboard after users visit the site

